    {
      "title": "SaaS Device Principal",
      "path": "docs/30-architecture/config-reference/saas-device-principal.md",
      "blocks": [
        {"kind": "paragraph", "text": "When `RIIDO_SAAS_URL` is selected with `RIIDO_DEVICE_ID` and `RIIDO_DEVICE_SECRET`, `saasplane` uses DevicePrincipal authentication."},
        {"kind": "paragraph", "text": "The daemon reports runtime snapshots to `/v1/daemon/runtime-snapshot`, polls `/v1/daemon/agent-bindings`, then polls the agent-specific assignment endpoint."},
        {"kind": "paragraph", "text": "Legacy `RIIDO_SAAS_AGENTS` and `RIIDO_SAAS_TOKEN` are not read by the daemon settings model."},
        {"kind": "paragraph", "text": "If `RIIDO_DAEMON_ID` is unset on this path, daemon id defaults to `RIIDO_DEVICE_ID`. This keeps runtime ids such as `device-enrolled-000123:codex` scoped to the enrolled device instead of `agentd-local:codex`."},
        {"kind": "paragraph", "text": "Desktop first enrolls the device through the logged-in webview session, then launches daemon with `RIIDO_DEVICE_ID` and `RIIDO_DEVICE_SECRET`. `saasplane` sends them as `X-Riido-Device-ID` and `X-Riido-Device-Secret`."},
        {"kind": "paragraph", "text": "Team IDs, Open API keys, task-context paths, and workspace API keys are not identity bridges."}
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "SaaS Polling And Runtime Bindings",
      "path": "docs/30-architecture/config-reference/saas-polling-runtime-bindings.md",
      "blocks": [
        {"kind": "paragraph", "text": "SaaS claim polling sends `PollRequest.wait_ms` with a built-in 30 second long-poll wait and extends HTTP timeout beyond that budget."},
        {"kind": "paragraph", "text": "This is not exposed as public env. `RIIDO_DAEMON_IDLE_POLL_INTERVAL_SECONDS` remains the local supervisor retry interval after empty long-poll responses."},
        {"kind": "paragraph", "text": "Dynamic runtime bindings from `/v1/daemon/agent-bindings` are cached for 5 seconds. Runtime registration/snapshot sync invalidates the cache so new provider facts appear promptly without making idle claim loops perform a one-request-per-second control-plane read."},
        {"kind": "paragraph", "text": "Runtime snapshots preserve local provider availability: explicit `provider.<name>.available=false` projects as `offline` or `missing`, not `online` merely because a binary was observed."}
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Agent Instruction Placement",
      "path": "docs/30-architecture/config-reference/agent-instruction-placement.md",
      "blocks": [
        {"kind": "paragraph", "text": "When a task is claimed, `saasplane` converts the control-plane assignment into a provider-neutral `TaskRequest`."},
        {"kind": "paragraph", "text": "The assignment-created `agent_instruction` snapshot and Riido telemetry contract are placed by provider capability:"},
        {"kind": "bullets", "items": [
          "Claude and OpenClaw use the system prompt surface.",
          "Codex and Cursor use a prompt prefix because current daemon surface does not rely on a separate system prompt channel."
        ]},
        {"kind": "paragraph", "text": "Placements are recorded in `TaskRequest.Metadata[\"riido_agent_instruction\"]` and `TaskRequest.Metadata[\"riido_telemetry_contract\"]` so tests can detect drift."},
        {"kind": "paragraph", "text": "The provider-specific placement matrix and real provider probe live in [`provider-runtime.md`](../../20-domain/provider-runtime.md#761-agent-instruction-placement-and-effectiveness-probe) and [`integration-matrix.md`](../integration-matrix.md#agent-instruction-effectiveness-probe)."}
      ]
    },
    {
